<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Operating Review </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Second Quarter </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Territory 1:
</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Acergy Northern Europe and Canada </I></B>&#150; Revenue from continuing operations for the second quarter was $121.1 million
(Q2 2009: $130.6 million) reflecting the ongoing challenging market environment and fewer projects in installation phase, partly offset by good operational progress on a number of projects including the DSVi frame agreement, DONG Trym, BP Skarv and
Deep Panuke. Net operating loss from continuing operations for the quarter was $5.0 million (Q2 2009: net operating loss of $4.5 million) reflecting lower activity levels due to prevailing market conditions, lower vessel utilisation and the
rescheduling of certain vessels for upcoming offshore operations. These factors were partially offset by the recognition of variation orders. Commercial negotiations on the Marathon Volund Project continue. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Acergy Asia and Middle East </I></B>&#150; Revenue from continuing operations for the second quarter was $81.3 million (Q2 2009: $53.7 million)
reflecting good progress on the Pluto Project. Net operating income from continuing operations for the quarter was $41.3 million (Q2 2009: $14.9 million) reflecting the successful completion of offshore operations on the Pluto and Pyrenees Projects,
partially offset by foreign exchange fluctuations. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Territory 2: </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Acergy Africa and Mediterranean</I></B> &#150; Revenue from continuing operations for the second quarter was $316.1 million (Q2 2009: $207.9
million) reflecting continued good operational progress on a number of major projects: Angola LNG, EPC4A, Block 15 and PazFlor, and a good contribution from Sonamet, which remained fully consolidated during the quarter although is classified as an
asset held for sale. Net operating income from continuing operations for the quarter was $83.1 million (Q2 2009: $41.1 million) due to good operational performance across the project portfolio, including Block 15, EPC4A, Angola LNG, PazFlor and
Sonamet. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Acergy North America and Mexico </I></B>&#150; Revenue from continuing operations for the second quarter was $0.4 million (Q2
2009: $29.2 million). Net operating loss from continuing operations for the quarter was $5.2 million (Q2 2009: net operating income of $8.1 million) as a result of the segment&#146;s operating cost base which was not covered by project activity.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Acergy South America</I></B><I> &#150; </I>Revenue from continuing operations for the second quarter was $60.3 million (Q2 2009: $100.7
million) reflecting lower activity levels due to the completion of the Frade SURF Project. This was partly offset by the four ships on long-term service agreements to Petrobras, which achieved full utilisation during the quarter outside of planned
dry-dock and the contribution from the Roncador Manifold Project. Net operating income from continuing operations for the quarter was $3.5 million (Q2 2009: $10.3 million) reflecting lower activity levels partly offset by strong performance from
<I>Acergy Condor</I>, <I>Pertinacia </I>and<I> Polar Queen</I>. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Acergy Corporate: </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Revenue from continuing operations for the second quarter was $1.7 million (Q2 2009: $3.4 million). Net operating loss from continuing operations for the
quarter was $24.0 million (Q2 2009: net operating income of $11.1 million) primarily due to the lower utilisation of corporate vessels, including <I>Acergy Eagle</I> and <I>Acergy Falcon</I> and reflects the transfer of the <I>Polar Queen</I> from
the Acergy Corporate segment to Acergy South America. Professional fees arising from the proposed combination, foreign exchange losses and ongoing legal restructuring and organisational optimisation were partially offset by positive contributions
from the SHL and NKT Flexibles joint ventures. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Discontinued operations </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net income from discontinued operations for the second quarter was $4.5 million (Q2 2009: $0.9 million) due to the positive contribution from the Mexilhao
Trunkline Project. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Asset Development </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Sonamet joint venture remained fully consolidated as at May&nbsp;31, 2010 although it continues to be classified as &#145;Assets held for sale&#146;.
After the completion of the sale and transfer of shares the business will be deconsolidated from Acergy&#146;s financials and its future results will be reported as share of results of associates and joint ventures. </FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As part of the ongoing fleet development programme, Acergy has acquired two vessels, post quarter end.
Firstly, the acquisition of <I>Antares</I>, a new shallow water barge for the Conventional market for pipelay and hook-up projects in West Africa. Secondly, the acquisition of <I>Polar </I>Queen, a flexible pipelay and subsea construction ship which
joined the fleet in 2006 on long-term charter, and which is currently on a long-term service agreement with Petrobras in Brazil. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Toisa
Proteus</I> was returned to her owner following the successful completion of offshore operations on the Pluto Project. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Financial Review
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Second Quarter </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Revenue from continuing operations for the second quarter was $581 million (Q2 2009: $526 million) primarily reflecting good activity levels in West
Africa and Asia Pacific, which were partially offset by lower activity levels in the North Sea, Brazil and Gulf of Mexico. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Gross profit was
$163 million (Q2 2009: $128 million) due to higher activity levels and a strong operating performance driven by good project execution, particularly in West Africa and Asia Pacific. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Administrative expenses were $74 million (Q2 2009: $55 million) due to the effect of foreign currency translation, higher professional fees arising from
the proposed combination with Subsea 7 Inc., ongoing legal restructuring and organisational optimisation and higher tendering costs. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Acergy&#146;s share of results of associates and joint ventures was $4 million (Q2 2009: $9 million) reflecting a positive consolidated contribution from
NKT Flexibles, Seaway Heavy Lifting and SapuraAcergy. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Other gains and losses was a gain of $5 million (Q2 2009: $8 million) primarily
reflecting the effect of foreign exchange translation on short-term Euro inter-company and cash balances and realised hedging losses arising from the weakened Euro in the quarter. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Income before taxes from continuing operations for the second quarter was $95 million (Q2 2009: $85 million) primarily reflecting a strong operational
performance across the project portfolio. This was partly offset by lower activity levels in the North Sea, Brazil and Gulf of Mexico, lower vessel utilisation, and higher administrative expenses. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Taxation for the quarter was $32 million (Q2 2009: $9 million) resulting in an effective tax rate for the quarter of 34% (Q2 2009: 11%) reflecting the
current geographical portfolio mix of our business. The effective tax rate for Q2 2009 reflects the release of certain provisions following the resolution of a number of audits during that quarter. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Income from continuing operations for the second quarter was $63 million (Q2 2009: $76 million). Net income from total operations for the second quarter
was $67 million (Q2 2009: $77 million). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The cash and cash equivalents position at the quarter end was $631 million (February 28 2010: $667
million) reflecting working capital outflows and the capital expenditure on <I>Acergy Borealis</I>, which will be funded entirely from the Company&#146;s existing cash resources. Deferred revenue at the quarter end stood at $227 million (February
28, 2010: $232 million). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">At May&nbsp;31, 2010, Acergy S.A. held directly 10,537,524 treasury shares representing 5.41% of the total number of
issued shares, as well as indirectly holding 879,121 treasury shares, representing 0.45% of the total number of issued shares, of which 573,000 are held in an employee benefit trust to support the 2009 Long-Term Incentive Plan. Total shares in issue
were 194,953,972, including treasury shares. </FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Backlog </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Backlog for continuing operations as at May&nbsp;31, 2010 was approximately $2.3 billion, of which approximately $0.9 billion is expected to be executed
in the fiscal year 2010. This figure does not include backlog related to associates and joint ventures. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Pre-Backlog</I>
</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">(2)</SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>205</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">309</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">99</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="line-height:8px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:0.5pt solid #000000;width:10%">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(1)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Backlog excludes amounts related to discontinued operations as of May.31.10: $15 million, Feb.28.09: $25 million, May.31.09: $77 million </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(2)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Pre-backlog reflects the stated value of letters of intent and the expected value of escalations on frame agreements </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Trading Outlook </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The more stable oil
price and strong tendering continues to underpin confidence in our business. However, for shorter-term work, particularly in the North Sea, the pricing environment remains competitive, and is likely to continue to impact margins in 2011. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Activity in the Conventional market in West Africa is expected to remain strong in the short and medium-term. A number of the major SURF contracts,
delayed during 2009, are still expected to come to market award in the second half of 2010. The offshore installation phase of these new SURF projects will commence beyond 2011. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We believe the trend will be for SURF projects to continue to increase in size and complexity which will contribute to substantial industry growth in the
medium-term. We are well placed to combine our competitive strengths of high calibre engineering and project management skills with our high quality assets to capture these growth opportunities. </FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ACERGY S.A. AND SUBSIDIARIES </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>SEGMENTAL ANALYSIS </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(In $ millions) </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Group has
six reportable segments based on the geographic distribution of its activities as follows: Acergy Northern Europe and Canada (NEC) includes all activities in Northern Europe and Eastern Canada; Acergy Asia and Middle East (AME) includes all
activities in Asia Pacific, India and the Middle East and including the SapuraAcergy joint venture, Acergy Africa and Mediterranean (AFMED) covers activities in Africa and the Mediterranean; Acergy North America and Mexico (NAMEX) includes all
activities in the United States, Mexico, Central America and Western Canada; Acergy South America (SAM) incorporates activities in South America and the islands of the southern Atlantic Ocean, Acergy Corporate (Corporate) includes all activities
that serve more than one region. These include the activities of the SHL and NKT joint ventures. Also included are assets which have global mobility including construction and flowline support ships, ROVs and other mobile assets that are not
attributed to any one segment; management of offshore personnel; captive insurance activities; Management and corporate services provided for the benefit of all of the Group&#146;s businesses. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">(1)</SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">
</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Four clients each individually accounted for more than 10% of the Group's revenue from continuing operations for the three months ended May&nbsp;31,
2010. The revenue from these clients was $318 million and was attributable to Acergy AFMED, Acergy AME and Acergy NAMEX. Three clients each individually accounted for more than 10% of the Group&#146;s revenue from continuing operations for the six
months ended May&nbsp;31, 2010. The revenue from these clients was $657 million and was attributable to Acergy AFMED, Acergy AME and Acergy NAMEX. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>

  <div STYLE="position: relative; left: auto; top: auto;">
<table id="pageTable" width="916" height="742" STYLE="position: relative; left: auto; top: auto;">
<tr>
<td nowrap>
<tr>
<td nowrap> <div style='position:absolute;left:13px;top:111px'>
<img src="g11342txs10gbgd.jpg" width="175" height="455" border="0" alt=""></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:14px;top:74px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:35px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#CE142C;'>Highlights</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:52px;top:129px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:27px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Solid quarterly performance:</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:94px;top:168px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:24px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Continuing operations:</div>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-right:1%; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The information set forth above shall be deemed to be incorporated by
reference into the prospectuses forming a part of&nbsp;our&nbsp;Registration Statements on Form S-8 (No. 33-85168, No.&nbsp;333-09292, No.&nbsp;333-74321, No.&nbsp;333-124983, No.&nbsp;333-124997 and No.&nbsp;333-166574)&nbsp;and our Registration
Statements on Form F-3 and Form F-3/A (No. 333-86288) and to be a part of such prospectuses&nbsp;from the date of the filing thereof. The attached press release and earnings presentation shall not be deemed &#147;filed&#148; for purposes of
Section&nbsp;18 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 or otherwise subject to the liabilities of that section, nor shall they be deemed incorporated by reference in any filing under the Securities Act of 1933, except as shall be expressly set forth
by specific reference in such filing. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Certain statements set forth above and contained in the press release and earnings
presentation furnished pursuant to this Form 6-K may include &#147;forward-looking statements&#148; within the meaning of Section&nbsp;27A of the Securities Act of 1933 and Section&nbsp;21E of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934. These statements
may be identified by the use of words like &#147;anticipate,&#148; &#147;believe,&#148; &#147;estimate,&#148; &#147;expect,&#148; &#147;intend,&#148; &#147;may,&#148; &#147;plan,&#148; &#147;forecast&#148;, &#147;project,&#148; &#147;will,&#148;
&#147;should,&#148; &#147;seek,&#148; and similar expressions. These statements include, but are not limited to, statements as to the approximate value of contract awards, expectations as to the Group&#146;s performance in 2010 and beyond, the
expected completion and benefits of the proposed combination with Subsea 7 Inc., the worldwide tendering activity and timing of industry contract awards, the continued commercial negotiations relating to the Marathon Volund Project, the impact of
the sale and deconsolidation of the Sonamet joint venture, the progress and funding of <I>Acergy Borealis</I>, expectations regarding <I>Antares</I>, expectations regarding our backlog and pre-backlog, statements contained in the &#147;Trading
Outlook&#148; section, including our visibility for 2010 and 2011, the expected impact of a continued competitive pricing environment, the anticipated activity levels in the Conventional market in West Africa, the activity levels in the North Sea
and Gulf of Mexico, the anticipated impact of the recent events in the Gulf of Mexico, the anticipation that delayed major SURF contracts will come to market and the timing of the offshore installation phase of such projects, the expectation for
SURF contracts to increase in size and complexity in the medium-term and our ability to capture growth opportunities. The forward-looking statements reflect our current views and assumptions and are subject to risks and uncertainties. The following
factors, and others which are discussed in our public filings and submissions with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, are among those that may cause actual and future results and trends to differ materially from our forward-looking
statements: actions by regulatory authorities or other third parties; unanticipated costs and difficulties related to the integration of Acergy S.A. and Subsea 7 Inc. and our ability to achieve benefits therefrom; unanticipated delays, costs and
difficulties related to the combination transaction, including satisfaction of closing conditions; our ability to recover costs on significant projects; the general economic conditions and competition in the markets and businesses in which we
operate; our relationship with significant clients; the outcome of legal and administrative proceedings or governmental enquiries; uncertainties inherent in operating internationally; the timely delivery of ships on order and the timely completion
of ship conversion programs; the impact of laws and regulations; and operating hazards, including spills and environmental damage. Many of these factors are beyond our ability to control or predict. Given these factors, you should not place undue
reliance on the forward-looking statements. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This communication does not constitute an offer to purchase, sell, or exchange or
the solicitation of an offer to sell, purchase, or exchange any securities of Subsea 7 Inc. or Acergy S.A. </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exhibit 99.1 </B></FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right">

<IMG SRC="g11342g57k50.jpg" ALT="LOGO"> </P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>Acergy S.A. Announces Second Quarter Results </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>London, England &#150; July&nbsp;14, 2010</B> &#150; Acergy S.A. (NASDAQ-GS: ACGY; Oslo Stock Exchange: ACY), announced today results for the second
quarter which ended on May&nbsp;31, 2010. The Group&#146;s accounts are prepared in accordance with International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS) as issued by the International Accounting Standards Board (IASB) and as adopted by the European
Union and were approved by the Board on July&nbsp;14, 2010. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Highlights </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Revenue from continuing operations was $581 million (Q2 2009: $526 million) </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Adjusted EBITDA</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">(</SUP>
</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">a)</SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"> from
 continuing operations was $121 million (Q2 2009: $113 million) corresponding to an Adjusted EBITDA margin of 20.9% (Q2 2009: 21.5%) </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Strong cash and cash equivalents position of $631 million (February 28, 2010: $667 million) </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Awarded $120 million Conventional contract, offshore Nigeria </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As part of our ongoing fleet development programme, Acergy acquired two vessels post quarter end; the <I>Polar Queen</I> and the <I>Antares</I>, a
shallow water barge for the West African Conventional market </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Post quarter end, on June&nbsp;21, 2010 the Boards of Directors of Acergy S.A. and Subsea 7 Inc. announced that they had agreed to combine the two
companies </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Jean Cahuzac, Chief Executive Officer, said: </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;We have delivered a solid quarterly performance driven by excellent project execution, additional variation orders on ongoing projects and strong
Conventional activity. We remain on track to deliver our 2010 expectations. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In line with our strategy to develop the fleet, we acquired the
<I>Antares</I> and <I>Polar Queen,</I> reinforcing our commitment to capture opportunities and invest in the business. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our announcement to
combine with Subsea 7 has been well received by clients, shareholders and our people. The combination will create a global leader in seabed-to-surface engineering and construction.&#148; </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Financial Summary </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD COLSPAN="1" NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Page&nbsp;1&nbsp;of&nbsp;12 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">



 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right">

<IMG SRC="g11342g57k50.jpg" ALT="LOGO"> </P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Operating Review </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Second Quarter </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Territory 1:
</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Acergy Northern Europe and Canada </I></B>&#150; Revenue from continuing operations for the second quarter was $121.1 million
(Q2 2009: $130.6 million) reflecting the ongoing challenging market environment and fewer projects in installation phase, partly offset by good operational progress on a number of projects including the DSVi frame agreement, DONG Trym, BP Skarv and
Deep Panuke. Net operating loss from continuing operations for the quarter was $5.0 million (Q2 2009: net operating loss of $4.5 million) reflecting lower activity levels due to prevailing market conditions, lower vessel utilisation and the
rescheduling of certain vessels for upcoming offshore operations. These factors were partially offset by the recognition of variation orders. Commercial negotiations on the Marathon Volund Project continue. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Acergy Asia and Middle East </I></B>&#150; Revenue from continuing operations for the second quarter was $81.3 million (Q2 2009: $53.7 million)
reflecting good progress on the Pluto Project. Net operating income from continuing operations for the quarter was $41.3 million (Q2 2009: $14.9 million) reflecting the successful completion of offshore operations on the Pluto and Pyrenees Projects,
partially offset by foreign exchange fluctuations. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Territory 2: </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Acergy Africa and Mediterranean</I></B> &#150; Revenue from continuing operations for the second quarter was $316.1 million (Q2 2009: $207.9
million) reflecting continued good operational progress on a number of major projects: Angola LNG, EPC4A, Block 15 and PazFlor, and a good contribution from Sonamet, which remained fully consolidated during the quarter although is classified as an
asset held for sale. Net operating income from continuing operations for the quarter was $83.1 million (Q2 2009: $41.1 million) due to good operational performance across the project portfolio, including Block 15, EPC4A, Angola LNG, PazFlor and
Sonamet. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Acergy North America and Mexico </I></B>&#150; Revenue from continuing operations for the second quarter was $0.4 million (Q2
2009: $29.2 million). Net operating loss from continuing operations for the quarter was $5.2 million (Q2 2009: net operating income of $8.1 million) as a result of the segment&#146;s operating cost base which was not covered by project activity.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Acergy South America</I></B><I> &#150; </I>Revenue from continuing operations for the second quarter was $60.3 million (Q2 2009: $100.7
million) reflecting lower activity levels due to the completion of the Frade SURF Project. This was partly offset by the four ships on long-term service agreements to Petrobras, which achieved full utilisation during the quarter outside of planned
dry-dock and the contribution from the Roncador Manifold Project. Net operating income from continuing operations for the quarter was $3.5 million (Q2 2009: $10.3 million) reflecting lower activity levels partly offset by strong performance from
<I>Acergy Condor</I>, <I>Pertinacia </I>and<I> Polar Queen</I>. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Acergy Corporate: </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Revenue from continuing operations for the second quarter was $1.7 million (Q2 2009: $3.4 million). Net operating loss from continuing operations for the
quarter was $24.0 million (Q2 2009: net operating income of $11.1 million) primarily due to the lower utilisation of corporate vessels, including <I>Acergy Eagle</I> and <I>Acergy Falcon</I> and reflects the transfer of the <I>Polar Queen</I> from
the Acergy Corporate segment to Acergy South America. Professional fees arising from the proposed combination, foreign exchange losses and ongoing legal restructuring and organisational optimisation were partially offset by positive contributions
from the SHL and NKT Flexibles joint ventures. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Discontinued operations </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net income from discontinued operations for the second quarter was $4.5 million (Q2 2009: $0.9 million) due to the positive contribution from the Mexilhao
Trunkline Project. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Asset Development </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Sonamet joint venture remained fully consolidated as at May&nbsp;31, 2010 although it continues to be classified as &#145;Assets held for sale&#146;.
After the completion of the sale and transfer of shares the business will be deconsolidated from Acergy&#146;s financials and its future results will be reported as share of results of associates and joint ventures. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Page&nbsp;2&nbsp;of&nbsp;12 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">



 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right">

<IMG SRC="g11342g57k50.jpg" ALT="LOGO"> </P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As part of the ongoing fleet development programme, Acergy has acquired two vessels, post quarter end.
Firstly, the acquisition of <I>Antares</I>, a new shallow water barge for the Conventional market for pipelay and hook-up projects in West Africa. Secondly, the acquisition of <I>Polar </I>Queen, a flexible pipelay and subsea construction ship which
joined the fleet in 2006 on long-term charter, and which is currently on a long-term service agreement with Petrobras in Brazil. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Toisa
Proteus</I> was returned to her owner following the successful completion of offshore operations on the Pluto Project. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Financial Review
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Second Quarter </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Revenue from continuing operations for the second quarter was $581 million (Q2 2009: $526 million) primarily reflecting good activity levels in West
Africa and Asia Pacific, which were partially offset by lower activity levels in the North Sea, Brazil and Gulf of Mexico. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Gross profit was
$163 million (Q2 2009: $128 million) due to higher activity levels and a strong operating performance driven by good project execution, particularly in West Africa and Asia Pacific. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Administrative expenses were $74 million (Q2 2009: $55 million) due to the effect of foreign currency translation, higher professional fees arising from
the proposed combination with Subsea 7 Inc., ongoing legal restructuring and organisational optimisation and higher tendering costs. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Acergy&#146;s share of results of associates and joint ventures was $4 million (Q2 2009: $9 million) reflecting a positive consolidated contribution from
NKT Flexibles, Seaway Heavy Lifting and SapuraAcergy. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Adjusted EBITDA margin from continuing operations for the three months was 20.9%
(Q2 2009: 21.5%). The Adjusted EBITDA margin from total operations for the three months was 21.9% (Q2 2009: 21.1%). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Other gains and losses
was a gain of $5 million (Q2 2009: $8 million) primarily reflecting the effect of foreign exchange translation on short-term Euro inter-company and cash balances and realised hedging losses arising from the weakened Euro in the quarter. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Income before taxes from continuing operations for the second quarter was $95 million (Q2 2009: $85 million) primarily reflecting a strong operational
performance across the project portfolio. This was partly offset by lower activity levels in the North Sea, Brazil and Gulf of Mexico, lower vessel utilisation, and higher administrative expenses. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Taxation for the quarter was $32 million (Q2 2009: $9 million) resulting in an effective tax rate for the quarter of 34% (Q2 2009: 11%) reflecting the
current geographical portfolio mix of our business. The effective tax rate for Q2 2009 reflects the release of certain provisions following the resolution of a number of audits during that quarter. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Income from continuing operations for the second quarter was $63 million (Q2 2009: $76 million). Net income from total operations for the second quarter
was $67 million (Q2 2009: $77 million). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The cash and cash equivalents position at the quarter end was $631 million (February 28 2010: $667
million) reflecting working capital outflows and the capital expenditure on <I>Acergy Borealis</I>, which will be funded entirely from the Company&#146;s existing cash resources. Deferred revenue at the quarter end stood at $227 million (February
28, 2010: $232 million). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">At May&nbsp;31, 2010, Acergy S.A. held directly 10,537,524 treasury shares representing 5.41% of the total number of
issued shares, as well as indirectly holding 879,121 treasury shares, representing 0.45% of the total number of issued shares, of which 573,000 are held in an employee benefit trust to support the 2009 Long-Term Incentive Plan. Total shares in issue
were 194,953,972, including treasury shares. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Page&nbsp;3&nbsp;of&nbsp;12 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Backlog </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Backlog for continuing operations as at May&nbsp;31, 2010 was approximately $2.3 billion, of which approximately $0.9 billion is expected to be executed
in the fiscal year 2010. This figure does not include backlog related to associates and joint ventures. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Trading Outlook </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The more stable oil
price and strong tendering continues to underpin confidence in our business. However, for shorter-term work, particularly in the North Sea, the pricing environment remains competitive, and is likely to continue to impact margins in 2011. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Activity in the Conventional market in West Africa is expected to remain strong in the short and medium-term. A number of the major SURF contracts,
delayed during 2009, are still expected to come to market award in the second half of 2010. The offshore installation phase of these new SURF projects will commence beyond 2011. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We believe the trend will be for SURF projects to continue to increase in size and complexity which will contribute to substantial industry growth in the
medium-term. We are well placed to combine our competitive strengths of high calibre engineering and project management skills with our high quality assets to capture these growth opportunities. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><B>***************************************************************************************************************************************
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Acergy S.A. is a seabed-to-surface engineering and construction contractor to the offshore oil and gas industry worldwide. We provide
integrated services, and we plan, design and deliver complex projects in harsh and challenging environments. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><B>*************************************************************************************************************************************** </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Page&nbsp;4&nbsp;of&nbsp;12 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">



 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right">

<IMG SRC="g11342g57k50.jpg" ALT="LOGO"> </P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="line-height:8px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:0.5pt solid #000000;width:10%">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">(a)</SUP></FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">
<P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex"></SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Adjusted
 EBITDA: </FONT></B><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Group calculates Adjusted EBITDA from continuing operations (adjusted earnings before interest, income taxation, depreciation and amortisation) as net income from continuing
operations plus finance costs, other gains and losses, taxation, depreciation and amortisation and adjusted to exclude investment income and impairment of property, plant and equipment and intangibles. Adjusted EBITDA margin from continuing
operations is defined as Adjusted EBITDA divided by revenue from continuing operations. Management believes that Adjusted EBITDA and Adjusted EBITDA margin from continuing operations are important indicators of our operational strength and the
performance of our business. Adjusted EBITDA and Adjusted EBITDA margin from continuing operations have not been prepared in accordance with International Financial Reporting Standards (&#147;IFRS&#148;) as issued by the IASB nor as adopted for use
in the European Union. These non-IFRS measures provide management with a meaningful comparison amongst our various regions, as they eliminate the effects of financing and depreciation. Adjusted EBITDA margin from continuing operations may also be a
useful ratio to compare our performance to our competitors and is widely used by shareholders and analysts following the Group&#146;s performance. However, Adjusted EBITDA and Adjusted EBITDA margin from continuing operations as presented by the
Group may not be comparable to similarly titled measures reported by other companies. Such supplementary adjustments to EBITDA may not be in accordance with current practices or the rules and regulations adopted by the US Securities and Exchange
Commission (the &#147;SEC&#148;) that apply to reports filed under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934. Accordingly, the SEC may require that Adjusted EBITDA and Adjusted EBITDA margin from continuing operations be presented differently in filings
made with the SEC than as presented in this release, or not be presented at all. Adjusted EBITDA and Adjusted EBITDA margin from continuing operations are not measures determined in accordance with IFRS and should not be considered as an alternative
to, or more meaningful than, net income (as determined in accordance with IFRS), as a measure of the Group&#146;s operating results or cash flows from operations (as determined in accordance with IFRS) or as a measure of the Group&#146;s liquidity.
The reconciliation of the Group&#146;s net income from continuing operations to Adjusted EBITDA from continuing operations is included in this release. This release also includes a supplemental calculation of Adjusted EBITDA from continuing
operations calculated as net operating income from continuing operations, plus depreciation and amortisation and impairment charges on property, plant and equipment and intangibles. Management believes that this supplemental presentation of Adjusted
EBITDA from continuing operations is also useful as it is more in line with the presentation of similarly titled measures by companies within Acergy&#146;s peer group and therefore believes it to be a helpful calculation for those evaluating
companies within Acergy&#146;s industry. Adjusted EBITDA for discontinued operations is calculated as per methodology outlined above. Adjusted EBITDA for total operations is the total of continuing operations and discontinued operations. </FONT>
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Forward-Looking Statements: </B>Certain statements made in this announcement may include &#147;forward-looking
statements&#148; within the meaning of Section&nbsp;27A of the Securities Act and Section&nbsp;21E of the US Securities Exchange Act of 1934. These statements may be identified by the use of words like &#147;anticipate,&#148; &#147;believe,&#148;
&#147;estimate,&#148; &#147;expect,&#148; &#147;intend,&#148; &#147;may,&#148; &#147;plan,&#148; &#147;forecast&#148;, &#147;project,&#148; &#147;will,&#148; &#147;should,&#148; &#147;seek,&#148; and similar expressions. These statements include,
but are not limited to, statements as to the approximate value of the contract award, expectations as to the Group&#146;s performance in 2010, the continued commercial negotiations relating to the Marathon Volund Project, the impact of the sale and
deconsolidation of the Sonamet joint venture, the funding of Acergy Borealis, expectations regarding our backlog and pre-backlog, statements contained in the &#147;Trading Outlook&#148; section, including our visibility for 2010 and 2011, the
expected impact of a continued competitive pricing environment, the anticipated activity levels in the Conventional market in West Africa, the anticipation that delayed major SURF contracts will come to market and the timing of the offshore
installation phase of such projects, the expectation for SURF contracts to increase in size and complexity in the medium-term and our ability to capture growth opportunities. The forward-looking statements reflect our current views and assumptions
and are subject to risks and uncertainties. The following factors, and others which are discussed in our public filings and submissions with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, are among those that may cause actual and future results and
trends to differ materially from our forward-looking statements: actions by regulatory authorities or other third parties; unanticipated costs and difficulties related to the integration of Acergy S.A. and Subsea 7 Inc. and our ability to achieve
benefits therefrom; unanticipated delays, costs and difficulties related to the combination transaction, including satisfaction of closing conditions; our ability to recover costs on significant projects; the general economic conditions and
competition in the markets and businesses in which we operate; our relationship with significant clients; the outcome of legal and administrative proceedings or governmental enquiries; uncertainties inherent in operating internationally; the timely
delivery of ships on order and the timely completion of ship conversion programmes; the impact of laws and regulations; and operating hazards, including spills and environmental damage. Many of these factors are beyond our ability to control or
predict. Given these factors, you should not place undue reliance on the forward-looking statements. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This communication does not constitute

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ACERGY S.A. AND SUBSIDIARIES </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>SEGMENTAL ANALYSIS </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(In $ millions) </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Group has
six reportable segments based on the geographic distribution of its activities as follows: Acergy Northern Europe and Canada (NEC) includes all activities in Northern Europe and Eastern Canada; Acergy Asia and Middle East (AME) includes all
activities in Asia Pacific, India and the Middle East and including the SapuraAcergy joint venture, Acergy Africa and Mediterranean (AFMED) covers activities in Africa and the Mediterranean; Acergy North America and Mexico (NAMEX) includes all
activities in the United States, Mexico, Central America and Western Canada; Acergy South America (SAM) incorporates activities in South America and the islands of the southern Atlantic Ocean, Acergy Corporate (Corporate) includes all activities
that serve more than one region. These include the activities of the SHL and NKT joint ventures. Also included are assets which have global mobility including construction and flowline support ships, ROVs and other mobile assets that are not
attributed to any one segment; management of offshore personnel; captive insurance activities; Management and corporate services provided for the benefit of all of the Group&#146;s businesses. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Four clients each individually accounted for more than 10% of the Group's revenue from continuing operations for the three months ended May&nbsp;31,
2010. The revenue from these clients was $318 million and was attributable to Acergy AFMED, Acergy AME and Acergy NAMEX. Three clients each individually accounted for more than 10% of the Group&#146;s revenue from continuing operations for the six
months ended May&nbsp;31, 2010. The revenue from these clients was $657 million and was attributable to Acergy AFMED, Acergy AME and Acergy NAMEX. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<div style='position:absolute;left:591px;top:156px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>are</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:622px;top:156px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>subject</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:683px;top:156px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>to</div>

<div style='position:absolute;left:746px;top:156px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>and</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:780px;top:156px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>uncertainties. </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:14px;top:172px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>The following factors, and others which are discussed in our public filings and submissions
with the U.S. Securities </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:14px;top:188px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>and Exchange Commission, are among those that may cause actual
and future results and trends to differ materially </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:14px;top:204px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>from our forward&#45;looking
statements: actions by regulatory authorities or other third parties; unanticipated costs </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:14px;top:220px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>and difficulties related to the integration of Acergy S.A. and Subsea 7 Inc. and our ability
to achieve benefits </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:14px;top:235px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>therefrom; unanticipated delays, costs and difficulties related to
the combination transaction, including satisfaction </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:14px;top:251px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>of closing conditions; our ability
to recover costs on significant projects; the general economic conditions and </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:14px;top:267px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>competition in the markets and businesses in which we operate; our relationship with
significant clients; the </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:14px;top:283px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>outcome of legal and administrative proceedings or
governmental enquiries; uncertainties inherent in operating </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:14px;top:299px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>internationally; the timely
delivery of ships on order and the timely completion of ship conversion programmes; the </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:14px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>impact</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:70px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>of</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:91px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>laws</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:130px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>and</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:163px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>regulations;</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:258px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>and</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:291px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>operating</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:367px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>hazards,</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:438px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>including</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:509px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>spills</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:552px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>and</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:585px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>environmental</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:698px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>damage.</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:775px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Many</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:821px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>of</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:842px;top:315px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>these </div>

not place undue reliance on the </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:14px;top:346px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>forward&#45;looking statements.</div>

<td nowrap> <div style='position:absolute;left:15px;top:40px'>
<img src="g11342ex99_2s24gbgd.jpg" width="877" height="608" border="0" alt=""></div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:16px;top:594px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>seabed&#45;to&#45;surface</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:16px;top:611px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>July 14, 2010</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:16px;top:627px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>slide 24</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:16px;top:3px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:35px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#CE142C;'>Adjusted EBITDA</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:108px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Group calculates Adjusted EBITDA from continuing operations (adjusted earnings before interest, income taxation, </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:123px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>depreciation and amortisation) as net income from continuing operations plus finance costs,
other gains and losses, taxation, depreciation and</div> <div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:137px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>amortisation and adjusted to exclude
investment income and impairment of property, plant and equipment and intangibles. Adjusted EBITDA </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:152px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>margin from continuing operations is defined as Adjusted EBITDA divided by revenue from
continuing operations.&nbsp; Management believes that </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:166px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Adjusted EBITDA and Adjusted
EBITDA margin from continuing operations are important indicators of our operational strength and the </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:181px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>performance of our business. Adjusted EBITDA and Adjusted EBITDA margin from continuing
operations have not been prepared in </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:195px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>accordance with International Financial Reporting
Standards (&#147;IFRS&#148;) as issued by the IASB nor as adopted for use in the European Union.&nbsp; </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:210px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>These non&#45;IFRS measures provide management with a meaningful comparison amongst our
various regions, as they eliminate the effects of </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:224px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>financing and depreciation.&nbsp;
Adjusted EBITDA margin from continuing operations may also be a useful ratio to compare our performance to </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:239px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>our competitors and is widely used by shareholders and analysts following the Group&#146;s
performance. However, Adjusted EBITDA and Adjusted</div> <div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:253px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>EBITDA margin from continuing
operations as presented by the Group may not be comparable to similarly titled measures reported by other </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:268px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>companies.&nbsp; Such supplementary adjustments to EBITDA may not be in accordance with
current practices or the rules and regulations </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:282px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>adopted by the US Securities and
Exchange Commission (the &#147;SEC&#148;) that apply to reports filed under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934.&nbsp; </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:297px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Accordingly, the SEC may require that Adjusted EBITDA and Adjusted EBITDA margin from
continuing operations be presented differently in </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:311px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>filings made with the SEC than as
presented in this release, or not be presented at all. Adjusted EBITDA and Adjusted EBITDA margin from </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:326px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>continuing operations are not measures determined in accordance with IFRS and should not be
considered as an alternative to, or more </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:340px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>meaningful than, net income (as determined in
accordance with IFRS), as a measure of the Group&#146;s operating results or cash flows from </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:355px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>operations (as determined in accordance with IFRS) or as a measure of the Group&#146;s
liquidity.&nbsp; The reconciliation of the Group&#146;s net income </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:369px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>from continuing
operations to Adjusted EBITDA from continuing operations is included in this release.&nbsp; This release also includes a </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:384px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>supplemental calculation of Adjusted EBITDA from continuing operations calculated as net
operating income from continuing operations, plus </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:398px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>depreciation and amortisation and
impairment charges on property, plant and equipment and intangibles.&nbsp; Management believes that this </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:413px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>supplemental presentation of Adjusted EBITDA from continuing operations is also useful as it
is more in line with the presentation of similarly </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:427px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>titled measures by companies within
Acergy&#146;s peer group and therefore believes it to be a helpful calculation for those evaluating companies </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:442px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>within Acergy&#146;s industry.&nbsp; Adjusted EBITDA for discontinued operations is calculated
as per methodology outlined above.&nbsp; Adjusted EBITDA for</div> <div style='position:absolute;left:38px;top:456px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>total operations is the
total of continuing operations and discontinued operations.<font size='3.2' face='"times new roman","times new roman",times,serif'> </font></div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:10px;top:108px;font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>(a)</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:41px;top:108px;font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Adjusted EBITDA:</div> </td></tr></table></div>
